www.papermag.com/rina-sawayama-karaoke-2563226483.html?rebelltitem=5#rebelltitem5 |accessdate=2020-04-22 |date=April 2018 |quote=Sawayama is an unapologetic fan of her genre. As she gushes over Avril Lavigne ("I love her so much"), Mariah Carey ("'Emotions' is a perfect ballad") Minogue ("Her discography is bangers!"), and Beyoncé ("I'm a Beyoncé stan, I've seen her live DVD about 20 times"), I also learn that she is, much like myself, fascinated by the way "pop music reflects politics." |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200709021807/https://www.papermag.com/rina-sawayama-karaoke-2563226483.html?rebelltitem=5#rebelltitem5 |archive-date=2020-07-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Escalante |first1=Shanti |title=RINA SAWAYAMA FINDS HER CHOSEN FAMILY |url=https://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/rina-sawayama-finds-her-chosen-family |website=Interview Magazine |accessdate=2020-04-22 |date=2020-04-17 |quote=I definitely want people to feel nostalgic. Maybe it's just hindsight, but I just feel like chart music back then was crazy diverse. There was obviously a huge thing of R&B that was going on. Then rock like No Doubt and then Limp Bizkit being number one for weeks in the UK. I remember that Evanescence was number one for weeks. Avril Lavigne, all these random people and then it was R&B and there was Justin Timberlake, Pharrell and Beyoncé and stuff. I just hope that people don't feel like it's being too referential. That's something I always want to try and stay away from. I always want to add something a bit new to the equation. Music from the 2000s was also the soundtrack to all this drama that I'm talking about the lyrics. I really wanted this record to sound like it was housed in the time when the things I'm talking about were happening. |archive-date=2020-08-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821041642/https://www.interviewmagazine.com/music/rina-sawayama-finds-her-chosen-family |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Rising Star Rina Sawayama's Music & Style Make Major Waves |url=https://www.thecoolhour.com/2019/07/rising-star-rina-sawayama-music-fashion-culture/ |website=The Cool Hour |accessdate=2020-04-22 |date=2019 |quote=She admits to falling in love with turn-of-the-century sensations like Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera, Avril Lavigne, and Pink, all who have had a positive influence on her own work |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200712174230/https://www.thecoolhour.com/2019/07/rising-star-rina-sawayama-music-fashion-culture/ |archive-date=2020-07-12 |dead-url=no }}</ref>等90和00年代的艺人影响。2017年，璃奈入选《卫报》的18年18强榜单，以及《{{le|Dazed|Dazed}}》的百强榜单<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2017/dec/31/18-for-18-the-talent-and-trends-tipped-for-the-top-in-2018|title=18 for '18: the talent and trends tipped for the top in 2018|last1=Williams|first1=Holly|last2=Brinkhurst-Cuff|first2=Charlie|date=2017-12-31|website=The Guardian|access-date=2018-07-13|last3=Fox|first3=Killian|last4=Snapes|first4=Laura|last5=Joshi|first5=Tara|last6=Cumming|first6=Laura|last7=Hans|first7=Simran|last8=Empire|first8=Kitty|last9=Devlin|first9=Hannah|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713202746/https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2017/dec/31/18-for-18-the-talent-and-trends-tipped-for-the-top-in-2018|archive-date=2018-07-13|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dazeddigital.com/dazed100/2017|title=100 people shaping culture in 2017|website=Dazed|access-date=2018-07-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712025344/http://www.dazeddigital.com/dazed100/2017|archive-date=2018-07-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>。为了唱更高的音，让歌聲有喘息聲，她用了Lady Gaga的[[美声唱法|美声唱法]]，一種義大利的歌劇練習法训练声乐<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Min|first=Lio|title=Rina Sawayama Breaks Through The Simulation|url=https://www.nylon.com/entertainment/rina-sawayama-on-sawayama-and-what-took-so-long|access-date=2020-06-11|website=Nylon|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611204418/https://www.nylon.com/enter